Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "pokuša" in different forms and positions:

1. On *pokušava* da reši ovaj problem. (He is *trying* to solve this problem.)
2. *Pokušaj* da ne kasniš na sastanak. (*Attempt* not to be late for the meeting.)
3. Oni su *pokušali* da pobegnu, ali su uhvaćeni. (They *tried* to escape, but they were caught.)
4. Da li si *pokušao* ovaj novi restoran? (Have you *tried* this new restaurant?)
5. Ako ne uspeš, uvek možeš da *pokušaš* ponovo. (If you don't succeed, you can always *try* again.)
6. Kada *pokušavam* da se usredsredim, uvek me nešto ometa. (When I'm *trying* to concentrate, something always distracts me.)
7. *Pokušaću* da dođem ranije. (*I will try* to come earlier.)
8. *Pokušajmo* da pronađemo rešenje zajedno. (*Let's try* to find a solution together.)
9. Ne mogu da *pokušam* ovo sam, treba mi tvoja pomoć. (I can't *attempt* this alone, I need your help.)
10. Njegov *pokušaj* da sakrije istinu nije uspeo. (His *attempt* to hide the truth was not successful.)

I hope these examples help!